The paper deals with wireless communication systems, specifically the downlink of a MIMO-OFDM system. It focuses on channel estimation and prediction, feedback, and scheduling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also deals with network infrastructure (base-station) and user terminals, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The scheduling algorithm is a key component of the paper, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions physical channel models, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of wireless systems, which suggests the category cs.COM (Computer Communications and Networks).
